1
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:08,709
- KATARA: Water.

2
00:00:09,709 --> 00:00:10,709
Earth.

3
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:12,625
Fire.

4
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:14,667
Air.

5
00:00:16,208 --> 00:00:20,250
Long ago, the four nations
lived together in harmony.

6
00:00:20,291 --> 00:00:23,333
Then, everything changed
when the Fire Nation attacked.

7
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:27,333
Only the Avatar,
master of all four elements,

8
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:28,875
could stop them.

9
00:00:28,917 --> 00:00:31,417
But when the world
needed him most, he vanished.

10
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:34,542
A hundred years passed,
and my brother and I discovered

11
00:00:34,583 --> 00:00:37,750
the new Avatar,
an Airbender named Aang.

12
00:00:37,792 --> 00:00:40,083
And although
his airbending skills are great,

13
00:00:40,125 --> 00:00:42,500
he has a lot to learn before
he's ready to save anyone.

14
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:44,000
- Ugh!

15
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:46,917
- KATARA: But I believe
Aang can save the world.

16
00:00:46,959 --> 00:00:50,458
♪

17
00:00:56,458 --> 00:00:59,917
- You have mastered
all four elements?

18
00:00:59,959 --> 00:01:02,583
- Yeah, and now
you're goin' down.

19
00:01:02,625 --> 00:01:04,083
- No!

20
00:01:04,125 --> 00:01:06,709
It is you
who are going down.

21
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:12,458
The comet is already here
and I'm unstoppable!

22
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:15,917
- The Avatar State
is a defense mechanism

23
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:19,041
designed to empower you with
the skills and knowledge

24
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:21,667
of all the past Avatars.

25
00:01:21,709 --> 00:01:26,041
The glow is the combination
of all your past lives,

26
00:01:26,083 --> 00:01:30,000
focusing their energy
through your body.

27
00:01:30,041 --> 00:01:33,583
- I can feel a lot of energy
twisted up around there.

28
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:35,166
Let me just see
if I can...

29
00:01:37,250 --> 00:01:38,709
- [thunder crashing]

30
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:42,917
- What happened generations
ago can be resolved now...

31
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:44,834
by you.

32
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:48,333
Born in you, along with
all this strife,

33
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:52,709
is the power to restore
balance to the world.

34
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,333
- After I leave here today,

35
00:01:54,375 --> 00:01:56,291
I'm gonna free
Uncle Iroh from his prison,

36
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,792
and I'm gonna beg
for his forgiveness.

37
00:01:58,834 --> 00:02:02,375
But I've come to an even
more important decision.

38
00:02:02,417 --> 00:02:04,333
I'm gonna join the Avatar,

39
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:06,125
and I'm going to
help him defeat you.

40
00:02:06,166 --> 00:02:07,709
Where is my uncle?

41
00:02:07,750 --> 00:02:09,500
- He busted himself out.

42
00:02:09,542 --> 00:02:11,000
- Sokka!

43
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,375
It's you!

44
00:02:14,041 --> 00:02:15,667
- AANG: We kissed
at the invasion,

45
00:02:15,709 --> 00:02:17,750
and I thought we were
gonna be together,

46
00:02:17,792 --> 00:02:18,959
but we're not.

47
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
- Aang...

48
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:22,333
I don't know.

49
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:24,625
- You miscalculated.

50
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:27,834
I love Zuko
more than I fear you.

51
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:29,625
- No, you miscalculated!

52
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:31,959
You should have
feared me more!

53
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,625
♪

54
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:37,208
- [heavy thud]

55
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:40,291
- You were right about
what Katara needed.

56
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:42,166
Violence wasn't the answer.

57
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:44,291
- It never is.

58
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:46,709
- Then I have
a question for you.

59
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,917
What are you gonna do
when you face my father?

60
00:02:48,959 --> 00:02:50,667
- [dramatic music]

61
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:55,750
♪

62
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:07,375
- More ferocious!

63
00:03:07,417 --> 00:03:09,041
Imagine striking through
your opponent's heart.

64
00:03:10,542 --> 00:03:12,500
- [groans]
I'm trying.

65
00:03:12,542 --> 00:03:15,667
- Now let me hear you roar
like tiger-dillo.

66
00:03:15,709 --> 00:03:17,291
- [quiet roar]

67
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:19,166
- That sounded pathetic.

68
00:03:19,208 --> 00:03:21,709
I said, roar!

69
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:25,041
- [roaring]

70
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:28,375
- [frightened chattering]

71
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:32,041
- Who wants a nice cool
glass of watermelon juice?

72
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,792
- Ooh, ooh, me, me, me!

73
00:03:33,834 --> 00:03:37,417
- Hey, your lesson's not
over yet! Get back here!

74
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:39,875
- Come on, Zuko,
just take a break.

75
00:03:39,917 --> 00:03:41,125
What's the big deal?

76
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:43,417
- Fine.

77
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:44,917
If you wanna
lounge around

78
00:03:44,959 --> 00:03:47,375
like a bunch of snail sloths
all day, then go ahead!

79
00:03:47,417 --> 00:03:49,959
- AANG: [slurping]
- Maybe Zuko's right.

80
00:03:50,041 --> 00:03:52,208
Sitting around the house
has made us pretty lazy.

81
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:54,166
But I know just the thing
to change that--

82
00:03:54,208 --> 00:03:56,375
Beach party!

83
00:03:56,417 --> 00:04:05,417
- ♪

84
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,500
- ♪

85
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:16,542
♪

86
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:18,166
- Check out my Appa
sand-sculpture.

87
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:19,250
- APPA:
[bellowing]

88
00:04:19,291 --> 00:04:21,625
- Not, bad baldy.

89
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:23,875
But I've been working
on my sandbending.

90
00:04:23,917 --> 00:04:25,041
You're gonna love this.

91
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:30,709
- ♪

92
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,625
- Whoa!

93
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:35,500
Wow, you even made a little
Earth King and Bosco.

94
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:39,667
- Try and top
that, Sokka.

95
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:42,792
- Ta-da!

96
00:04:42,834 --> 00:04:46,166
- AANG: Is that
a blubbering blob-monster?

97
00:04:46,208 --> 00:04:48,208
- No, it's Suki!

98
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:51,458
- BOTH:
[laughing]

99
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,166
- Suki, we'll
all understand

100
00:04:53,208 --> 00:04:55,166
if you break with
him up over this.

101
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:57,250
- I think it's sweet.

102
00:04:57,291 --> 00:04:58,542
- [smooching]

103
00:04:58,583 --> 00:04:59,959
- But it doesn't
even look like--

104
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,417
[screams]

105
00:05:02,834 --> 00:05:10,834
- ♪

106
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,375
- What are you doing?

107
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:19,291
- Teaching you a lesson.

108
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,917
- [dramatic music]

109
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:30,959
♪

110
00:05:33,792 --> 00:05:35,375
- What happened?

111
00:05:35,417 --> 00:05:37,208
- Zuko's gone crazy!

112
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:39,583
I made a sand sculpture
of Suki and he destroyed it!

113
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:43,041
Oh, and he's
attacking Aang.

114
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:51,083
- ♪

115
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,375
- ♪

116
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:01,917
♪

117
00:06:01,959 --> 00:06:05,041
- Get a grip before I blast
you off this roof!

118
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:06,709
- Go ahead and do it.

119
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:14,750
- ♪

120
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:22,709
- ♪

121
00:06:23,709 --> 00:06:31,709
♪

122
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:39,041
♪

123
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:40,625
- Enough!

124
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:44,208
- ♪

125
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:45,542
- [wood splintering]

126
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:47,667
- ZUKO:
[grunting]

127
00:06:47,709 --> 00:06:48,792
[groans]

128
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:52,291
- What's wrong with you?
You could have hurt Aang.

129
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:53,583
- What's wrong with me?

130
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:55,709
What's wrong with
all of you?

131
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,125
How can you sit around
having beach parties

132
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:59,667
when Sozin's comet
is only three days away?

133
00:07:02,166 --> 00:07:04,375
Why are you all looking
at me like I'm crazy?

134
00:07:04,417 --> 00:07:06,667
- About Sozin's comet--

135
00:07:06,709 --> 00:07:08,458
I was actually gonna
wait to fight the Firelord

136
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,083
until after it came.

137
00:07:10,125 --> 00:07:11,166
- After?

138
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:12,709
- I'm not ready.

139
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:14,792
I need more time
to master firebending.

140
00:07:14,834 --> 00:07:16,875
- And, frankly,
your earthbending

141
00:07:16,917 --> 00:07:18,792
could still use
some work, too.

142
00:07:18,834 --> 00:07:21,291
- So, you all knew
Aang was gonna wait?

143
00:07:21,333 --> 00:07:24,166
- Honestly, if Aang tries to
fight the Firelord right now,

144
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:25,834
he's gonna lose.

145
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:27,041
No offence.

146
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:28,333
- The whole point of
fighting the Firelord

147
00:07:28,375 --> 00:07:30,041
before the comet

148
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,125
was to stop the Fire Nation
from winning the war.

149
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:35,250
But they pretty much won the war
when they took Ba Sing Se.

150
00:07:35,291 --> 00:07:37,333
Things can't get any worse.

151
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:39,917
- You're wrong.

152
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:42,667
It's about to get worse
than you can even imagine.

153
00:07:42,709 --> 00:07:44,333
The day before the eclipse,

154
00:07:44,375 --> 00:07:47,375
my father asked me to attend
an important war meeting.

155
00:07:47,417 --> 00:07:50,792
It was what I'd dreamed about
and wanted for so many years.

156
00:07:50,834 --> 00:07:52,625
My father had finally
accepted me back.

157
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,333
- Welcome, Prince Zuko.

158
00:07:58,375 --> 00:08:00,125
We waited for you.

159
00:08:07,709 --> 00:08:10,333
General Shinu,
your report.

160
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:12,959
- Thank you, sir.

161
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,417
Ba Sing Se is still
under our control,

162
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:18,333
however, Earthbender
rebellions have prevented us

163
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:21,458
from achieving total victory
in the Earth Kingdom.

164
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,583
- What is
your recommendation?

165
00:08:23,625 --> 00:08:25,375
- Our army is spread too thin,

166
00:08:25,417 --> 00:08:28,458
but once the eclipse is over,
and the invasion defeated,

167
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:32,291
we should transfer more domestic
forces into the Earth Kingdom.

168
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:34,291
- Mmm...

169
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:37,125
Prince Zuko, you've been among
the Earth Kingdom commoners.

170
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,458
Do you think that
adding more troops

171
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,667
will stop these rebellions?

172
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:46,417
- The people of the Earth
Kingdom are proud and strong.

173
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:50,375
They can endure anything
as long as they have hope.

174
00:08:50,417 --> 00:08:51,875
- Yes, you're right.

175
00:08:53,542 --> 00:08:56,750
We need to destroy
their hope.

176
00:08:56,792 --> 00:08:58,792
- Well, that's not
exactly what I--

177
00:08:58,834 --> 00:09:01,125
- I think you should take
their precious hope,

178
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:05,583
and the rest of their land
and burn it all to the ground.

179
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:09,583
- Yes, yes,
you're right Azula.

180
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:12,542
Sozin's comet
is almost upon us,

181
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:14,250
And on that day,
it will endow us

182
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:17,875
with the strength
and power of a hundred suns.

183
00:09:17,917 --> 00:09:20,375
No bender will stand
a chance against us.

184
00:09:20,417 --> 00:09:23,208
- What are suggesting, sir?

185
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:26,959
- When the comet last came,
my grandfather, Firelord Sozin,

186
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,291
used it to wipe
out the Air Nomads.

187
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:33,083
Now, I will use its power
to end the Earth Kingdom--

188
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:34,583
permanently!

189
00:09:36,291 --> 00:09:40,041
From our airships we will
rain fire over their lands,

190
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:43,834
a fire that will
destroy everything,

191
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:47,250
and out of the ashes,
a new world will be born,

192
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:50,709
a world in which all
the lands are Fire Nation,

193
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:55,208
and I am the supreme
ruler of everything!

194
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:56,750
- ALL:
[applauding]

195
00:09:56,792 --> 00:09:58,542
- ZUKO:
I wanted to speak out

196
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:00,083
against this
horrifying plan,

197
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:02,041
but I'm ashamed
to say I didn't.

198
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:03,291
My whole life,
I've struggled

199
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,834
to gain my father's
love and acceptance.

200
00:10:05,875 --> 00:10:07,375
But once I had it,

201
00:10:07,417 --> 00:10:10,333
I realized I'd lost myself
getting there.

202
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:13,250
I'd forgotten who I was.

203
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:15,750
- I can't believe this.

204
00:10:15,792 --> 00:10:18,000
- I always knew the Firelord
was a bad guy.

205
00:10:18,041 --> 00:10:21,333
But his plan
is just pure evil.

206
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:23,458
- What am I gonna do?

207
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:25,333
- I know you're scared.

208
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:28,208
And I know you're not
ready to save the world.

209
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,041
But if you don't defeat the
Firelord before the comet comes,

210
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:32,291
there won't be a world
to save anymore.

211
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:33,792
- [dramatic music]

212
00:10:37,625 --> 00:10:40,583
- Why didn't you tell me about
your dad's crazy plan sooner?

213
00:10:40,625 --> 00:10:42,250
- I didn't think I had to.

214
00:10:42,291 --> 00:10:44,709
I assumed you were still gonna
fight him before the comet.

215
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:47,083
No one told me you
decided to wait.

216
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:48,500
- This is bad.

217
00:10:48,542 --> 00:10:51,000
This is really,
really bad.

218
00:10:51,041 --> 00:10:54,208
- Aang, you don't have
to do this alone.

219
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,792
- Yeah, if we all fight
the Firelord together,

220
00:10:56,834 --> 00:10:58,583
we've got a shot
at taking him down.

221
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,417
- All right!
Team Avatar is back!

222
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:02,917
Air.

223
00:11:02,959 --> 00:11:03,917
Water.

224
00:11:03,959 --> 00:11:05,166
Earth.

225
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:06,375
Fire.

226
00:11:06,417 --> 00:11:08,583
Fan and sword.

227
00:11:09,542 --> 00:11:11,166
- Fighting the Firelord

228
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:13,333
is gonna be the hardest thing
we've ever done together.

229
00:11:13,375 --> 00:11:15,709
But I wouldn't wanna
do it any other way.

230
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,542
- ALL EXCEPT ZUKO:
[laughing]

231
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:19,667
- Yeah.
- All right.

232
00:11:19,709 --> 00:11:21,333
- Get over here, Zuko.

233
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:22,834
Being part of the group

234
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:24,917
also means being part
of group hugs.

235
00:11:28,792 --> 00:11:30,458
- APPA:
[bellowing]

236
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,792
- [heavy thud]

237
00:11:33,625 --> 00:11:35,458
- There is one technique
you need to know

238
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:36,542
before facing
my father--

239
00:11:36,583 --> 00:11:38,166
how to redirect
lightning.

240
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,709
If you let the energy
in your own body flow,

241
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:44,250
the lightning will
follow it.

242
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:46,792
You turn your opponents'
energy against them.

243
00:11:46,834 --> 00:11:49,333
- That's like waterbending.
- Exactly.

244
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,417
My uncle invented
this technique himself

245
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:53,000
by studying Waterbenders.

246
00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:56,291
- So, have you ever
redirected lightning before?

247
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:57,542
- Once...

248
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:58,875
against my father.

249
00:11:58,917 --> 00:12:01,250
- What did it feel like?

250
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:02,375
- Exhilarating.

251
00:12:02,417 --> 00:12:05,250
- [electrical zapping]

252
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:06,291
- But terrifying.

253
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:07,208
- [electrical zapping]

254
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,000
- [explosion]

255
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:13,041
- You feel so powerful holding
that much energy in your body,

256
00:12:13,083 --> 00:12:16,291
but you know if you make
the wrong move--it's over.

257
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:19,542
- [laughs]
Well, not over-over.

258
00:12:19,583 --> 00:12:21,333
I mean,
there is always Katara

259
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:24,000
and a little spirit water
action, am I right?

260
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:27,208
- Actually, I used it all
up after Azula shot you.

261
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:29,208
- Oh.

262
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:32,000
- You'll have to take Firelord's
life before he takes yours.

263
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:35,917
- Yeah, I'll just
do that.

264
00:12:42,792 --> 00:12:44,375
- SOKKA: Gather around,
Team Avatar.

265
00:12:46,834 --> 00:12:48,625
In order to take
out the Firelord,

266
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:50,458
or, in this case,
the Melonlord,

267
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:52,667
our timing has
to be perfect.

268
00:12:52,709 --> 00:12:55,166
First, Suki and I will
draw his fire.

269
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:58,875
Then Katara and Zuko charge in
with some liquidy hot offence,

270
00:12:58,917 --> 00:13:00,959
and while the Melonlord
is distracted,

271
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:05,166
Aang swoops in and "bam,"
he delivers the final blow.

272
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:07,333
- Uh, what about me?

273
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:09,333
- For now, you're
the Melonlord's forces.

274
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:11,834
- So, I get to chuck
flaming rocks at all of you?

275
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:14,709
- Whatever makes the training
field more realistic.

276
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:17,083
- Sweetness.

277
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:19,000
Mwa-ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!

278
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:27,041
- ♪

279
00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:35,667
- ♪

280
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:43,333
♪

281
00:13:43,375 --> 00:13:46,291
- [flames crackling]

282
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:47,792
- Watch it, Toph!

283
00:13:47,834 --> 00:13:51,250
- I am not Toph,
I am Melonlord!

284
00:13:51,291 --> 00:13:53,417
Mwa-ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!

285
00:13:53,458 --> 00:14:01,458
- ♪

286
00:14:06,959 --> 00:14:08,250
- Now, Aang.

287
00:14:08,291 --> 00:14:16,041
- ♪

288
00:14:19,709 --> 00:14:21,917
- What are you waiting for?
Take him out!

289
00:14:21,959 --> 00:14:23,291
- I can't.

290
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,458
- What's wrong with you?

291
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,125
If this was
the real deal,

292
00:14:29,166 --> 00:14:31,333
you'd be shot full
of lightning right now.

293
00:14:31,375 --> 00:14:33,792
- I'm sorry, but it just
didn't feel right.

294
00:14:33,834 --> 00:14:35,250
I didn't feel
like myself.

295
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:39,500
- [watermelon splats]

296
00:14:39,542 --> 00:14:40,875
- There!
That's how it's done.

297
00:14:42,792 --> 00:14:44,291
- [nibbling]

298
00:14:54,709 --> 00:14:56,875
- I have a surprise
for everyone!

299
00:14:56,917 --> 00:14:59,583
- I knew it! You did have
a secret thing with Haru!

300
00:15:02,375 --> 00:15:04,333
- Uh...no.

301
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:08,000
I was looking for cooking pots
in the attic and I found this.

302
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:12,375
Look at baby Zuko!
Isn't he cute?

303
00:15:12,417 --> 00:15:15,542
- ALL EXCEPT ZUKO:
[laughing]

304
00:15:15,583 --> 00:15:17,542
- Oh, lighten up.
I'm just teasing.

305
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:20,625
That's not me.
It's my father.

306
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:24,792
- But he looks so sweet
and innocent.

307
00:15:24,834 --> 00:15:27,667
- Well, that sweet little kid
grew up to be a monster.

308
00:15:27,709 --> 00:15:30,125
And the worst father in
the history of fathers.

309
00:15:30,166 --> 00:15:32,583
- AANG: But he's still
a human being.

310
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:34,250
- You're going to
defend him?

311
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:36,417
- No, I agree with you.

312
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:38,542
Firelord Ozai
is a horrible person,

313
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,709
and the world will probably
be better off without him,

314
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,542
but there's gotta
be another way.

315
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:43,959
- Like what?

316
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,250
- I don't know.

317
00:15:45,291 --> 00:15:47,709
Maybe we can make
some big pots of glue

318
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,083
and then I can
use gluebending

319
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:50,500
to stick his arms
and legs together

320
00:15:50,542 --> 00:15:52,000
so he can't bend anymore.

321
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:54,125
- Yeah, then you can show
him his baby pictures

322
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:56,250
and all those happy memories
will make him good again.

323
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:58,000
- Do you really think
that would work?

324
00:15:58,041 --> 00:15:59,959
- No!
- [heavy sigh]

325
00:16:01,917 --> 00:16:04,834
This goes against everything
I learned from the monks.

326
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:07,667
I can't just go around wiping
out people I don't like.

327
00:16:07,709 --> 00:16:10,083
- Sure, you can.
You're the Avatar.

328
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:11,750
If it's in the name
of keeping balance,

329
00:16:11,792 --> 00:16:14,458
I'm pretty sure the universe
will forgive you.

330
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,542
- This isn't
a joke, Sokka!

331
00:16:16,583 --> 00:16:18,917
None of you understand
the position I'm in!

332
00:16:18,959 --> 00:16:21,083
- Aang, we do understand.
It's just--

333
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:23,000
- Just what, Katara, what?

334
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:24,750
- We're trying to help.

335
00:16:24,792 --> 00:16:27,291
- When you figure out a way
for me to beat the Firelord

336
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,291
without taking his life,
I'd love to hear it!

337
00:16:31,542 --> 00:16:34,875
- Aang, don't walk
away from this.

338
00:16:34,917 --> 00:16:37,417
- Let him go.

339
00:16:37,458 --> 00:16:40,000
He needs time to sort
it out by himself.

340
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:48,041
- ♪

341
00:16:54,041 --> 00:16:55,500
- ♪

342
00:16:55,542 --> 00:16:57,125
- [chattering]

343
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:58,583
- Hey, Momo.

344
00:16:58,625 --> 00:17:01,125
I don't suppose you know
what I should do.

345
00:17:01,166 --> 00:17:02,500
- [squawks]

346
00:17:02,542 --> 00:17:03,917
- I didn't think so.

347
00:17:03,959 --> 00:17:11,959
- ♪

348
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:21,750
- MEN: [deep-toned
hypnotic chanting]

349
00:17:21,792 --> 00:17:30,792
- ♪

350
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:38,583
- [hypnotic chanting
continues]

351
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:47,625
- ♪

352
00:17:47,667 --> 00:17:50,000
- [hypnotic chanting
continues]

353
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:54,583
- ♪

354
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:01,542
- SOKKA:
Okay, that's everything.

355
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:03,709
- No, it's not.
Where's Aang?

356
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:11,375
- Aang? Aang?

357
00:18:11,417 --> 00:18:13,291
- Come on, lazy bones,
let's go!

358
00:18:15,166 --> 00:18:16,542
- [door creaks, thuds]

359
00:18:27,125 --> 00:18:28,875
- He left his staff.

360
00:18:28,917 --> 00:18:30,166
That's so strange.

361
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:32,250
- Aang's not in a house.
Let's check the beach.

362
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:37,917
- SOKKA: Look! There's
his footprints.

363
00:18:37,959 --> 00:18:39,875
The trail ends here.

364
00:18:39,917 --> 00:18:43,166
- So, he went for a midnight
swim and never came back?

365
00:18:43,208 --> 00:18:44,792
- Maybe he was captured.

366
00:18:44,834 --> 00:18:47,250
- I don't think so.
There's no sign of a struggle.

367
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:49,041
- I bet he ran away again.

368
00:18:49,083 --> 00:18:51,750
- Unh-unh. He left behind
his glider and Appa.

369
00:18:51,792 --> 00:18:53,333
- Then what do you think's

370
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:55,500
happened to him,
oh, sleuthy one?

371
00:18:55,542 --> 00:18:57,500
- It's pretty obvious.

372
00:18:57,542 --> 00:19:00,166
Aang mysteriously disappears
before an important battle?

373
00:19:00,208 --> 00:19:02,792
He's definitely on
a spirit world journey.

374
00:19:02,834 --> 00:19:05,667
- But if he was, wouldn't
his body still be here?

375
00:19:05,709 --> 00:19:07,542
- Oh, yeah,
I forgot about that.

376
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:09,542
- Then he's gotta be
somewhere on Ember Island.

377
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:11,500
Let's split up
and look for him.

378
00:19:11,542 --> 00:19:13,250
- I'm going with Zuko!

379
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:15,083
What?

380
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:17,291
Everyone else went on a life-
changing field-trip with Zuko.

381
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:18,500
Now, it's my turn.

382
00:19:18,542 --> 00:19:26,542
- ♪

383
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:28,875
- CROWD:
[chanting "Aang! Aang!"]

384
00:19:32,208 --> 00:19:34,250
[chanting continues]

385
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:39,208
- Avatar State, yip-yip!
- CROWD: [cheering]

386
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:40,792
- BOTH:
[growling]

387
00:19:40,834 --> 00:19:43,625
- TOPH: And then when I was
nine, I ran away again.

388
00:19:43,667 --> 00:19:45,875
- Uh-huh.
- I know I shouldn't complain.

389
00:19:45,917 --> 00:19:48,500
My parents gave me
everything I ever asked for.

390
00:19:48,542 --> 00:19:51,542
But they never gave the one
thing that I really wanted--

391
00:19:51,583 --> 00:19:52,959
their love,
you know what I mean?

392
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
- [groans]

393
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:57,250
Look, I know you
had a rough childhood.

394
00:19:57,291 --> 00:20:00,583
But we should really
focus on finding Aang.

395
00:20:00,625 --> 00:20:03,375
- This is the worst
field trip ever.

396
00:20:03,417 --> 00:20:05,000
[blows air]

397
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:12,333
- Judging by the looks
on your faces,

398
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:15,875
I'm guessing you guys
didn't find Aang, either.

399
00:20:15,917 --> 00:20:17,792
- No.

400
00:20:17,834 --> 00:20:20,375
It's like he just
disappeared.

401
00:20:20,417 --> 00:20:21,959
- Hey, wait a minute.

402
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,166
Has anyone noticed that
Momo is missing, too?

403
00:20:24,208 --> 00:20:28,041
- Oh, no! I knew it
was only a matter of time!

404
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:31,625
Appa ate Momo!

405
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:34,291
Momo, I'm coming
for you, buddy!

406
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:38,542
- Sokka, Appa didn't eat Momo.
He's probably with Aang.

407
00:20:38,583 --> 00:20:41,750
- That's just what Appa
wants you to think.

408
00:20:41,792 --> 00:20:43,875
- ZUKO: Get out of
the bison's mouth, Sokka.

409
00:20:43,917 --> 00:20:45,667
We have a real problem here.

410
00:20:45,709 --> 00:20:48,834
Aang is nowhere to be found and
the comet is only two days away.

411
00:20:48,875 --> 00:20:51,667
- What should we do, Zuko?

412
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:53,125
- I don't know.

413
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:57,959
Why are you all
looking at me?

414
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,917
- Well, you are kind of
the expert on tracking Aang.

415
00:21:00,959 --> 00:21:03,125
- Yeah, if anyone's
got experience

416
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:05,000
hunting the Avatar,
it's you.

417
00:21:09,834 --> 00:21:12,041
- Zuko, I don't wanna tell
you how to do your job,

418
00:21:12,083 --> 00:21:14,500
but why we are heading
towards the Earth Kingdom?

419
00:21:14,542 --> 00:21:16,208
There's no way
Aang's there.

420
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,041
- Just trust me.

421
00:21:18,083 --> 00:21:26,083
- ♪

422
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,041
- ♪

423
00:21:34,792 --> 00:21:37,458
♪

424
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,583
- Come on,
slowpokes, faster!

425
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:47,625
- ♪

426
00:21:54,542 --> 00:21:55,625
- ♪

427
00:21:56,625 --> 00:22:01,166
♪

428
00:22:01,208 --> 00:22:02,875
- Sorry I'm late, Father.

429
00:22:02,917 --> 00:22:06,583
Good palanquin bearers are
so hard to come by these days.

430
00:22:06,625 --> 00:22:09,250
So, is everything ready
for our departure?

431
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:11,583
- There has been a change
of plans, Azula.

432
00:22:11,625 --> 00:22:13,250
- What?

433
00:22:13,291 --> 00:22:16,750
- I've decided to lead the fleet
of airships to Ba Sing Se alone.

434
00:22:16,792 --> 00:22:20,667
You will remain here
in the Fire Nation.

435
00:22:20,709 --> 00:22:23,375
- But, I thought we were
going to do this together.

436
00:22:23,417 --> 00:22:26,583
- My decision is final.

437
00:22:26,625 --> 00:22:29,250
- You...you can't
treat me like this!

438
00:22:29,291 --> 00:22:31,208
You can't treat
me like Zuko!

439
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:33,834
- Azula, silence yourself.

440
00:22:33,875 --> 00:22:36,458
- But it was my idea to burn
everything to the ground.

441
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:38,375
I deserve to be
by your side!

442
00:22:38,417 --> 00:22:41,208
- Azula!

443
00:22:41,250 --> 00:22:42,583
Listen to me.

444
00:22:42,625 --> 00:22:45,583
I need you here to watch
over the homeland.

445
00:22:45,625 --> 00:22:50,000
It's a very important job that
I can only entrust to you.

446
00:22:50,041 --> 00:22:51,750
- Really?

447
00:22:51,792 --> 00:22:54,000
- And for your loyalty,

448
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:58,208
I've decided to declare
you the new Firelord.

449
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:00,458
- Firelord Azula?

450
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:03,250
It does seems appropriate.

451
00:23:03,291 --> 00:23:05,250
But, what about you?

452
00:23:05,291 --> 00:23:08,709
- Firelord Ozai is no more.

453
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:11,875
Just as the world will
be reborn in fire,

454
00:23:11,917 --> 00:23:16,500
I shall be reborn as
the supreme ruler of the world.

455
00:23:16,542 --> 00:23:20,250
From this moment on,
I will be known as...

456
00:23:20,291 --> 00:23:22,083
The Phoenix King!

457
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:25,125
♪

458
00:23:39,375 --> 00:23:44,333
♪

459
00:23:49,542 --> 00:23:51,792
- TAVERN PATRONS:
[shouting mixed comments]

460
00:23:54,250 --> 00:23:55,625
- And the reason
you brought us

461
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:58,000
to a seedy Earth Kingdom
tavern is what now?

462
00:23:58,041 --> 00:23:59,542
- Jun.

463
00:24:01,291 --> 00:24:03,333
- MAN:
[groans]

464
00:24:03,375 --> 00:24:05,250
- SOKKA: Oh, yeah,
that weird bounty hunter

465
00:24:05,291 --> 00:24:06,709
with the giant mole.

466
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:08,792
- KATARA: Mole?
Her skin is flawless.

467
00:24:08,834 --> 00:24:10,291
- SOKKA: No, she has this
giant mole-creature

468
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,208
she rides around on.

469
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:13,500
- The Shirshu.

470
00:24:13,542 --> 00:24:15,417
It's the only animal that
can track Aang's scent

471
00:24:15,458 --> 00:24:16,834
anywhere in the world.

472
00:24:16,875 --> 00:24:19,000
It's the one shot
we have of finding him.

473
00:24:19,041 --> 00:24:20,709
- MAN:
[grunting]

474
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:35,375
- I don't know who this
Jun lady is, but I like her.

475
00:24:35,417 --> 00:24:40,000
- [chattering]

476
00:24:40,041 --> 00:24:42,583
[licking]
- [groaning]

477
00:24:42,625 --> 00:24:45,625
Hey, Momo. I just had
the strangest dream.

478
00:24:48,959 --> 00:24:51,125
Wait!

479
00:24:51,166 --> 00:24:53,166
- [chattering]

480
00:24:53,208 --> 00:25:00,166
- ♪

481
00:25:00,208 --> 00:25:01,125
- AANG:
Where are we?

482
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:02,792
- [dramatic music]

483
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:09,709
- ♪

484
00:25:15,041 --> 00:25:18,709
- Hey, I remember her.
She helped you attack us.

485
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:20,750
- Yep. Back in
the good old days.

486
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:24,709
- JUN: Oh, great,
it's Prince Pouty.

487
00:25:24,750 --> 00:25:26,166
Where's your
creepy grandpa?

488
00:25:26,208 --> 00:25:28,000
- He's my uncle.

489
00:25:28,041 --> 00:25:30,000
And he's not here.

490
00:25:30,041 --> 00:25:32,250
- I see you worked things
out with your girlfriend.

491
00:25:32,291 --> 00:25:34,625
- I'm not his girlfriend!
- She's not my girlfriend!

492
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:38,500
- Okay, okay. Sheesh.
I was only teasing.

493
00:25:38,542 --> 00:25:39,875
So what do you want?

494
00:25:39,917 --> 00:25:41,875
- I need your help
finding the Avatar.

495
00:25:41,917 --> 00:25:44,500
- Hm, doesn't
sound too fun.

496
00:25:46,083 --> 00:25:49,125
- Does the end of the world
sound like more fun?

497
00:25:49,166 --> 00:25:51,166
- APPA:
[growling]

498
00:25:51,208 --> 00:25:52,792
[slurping]

499
00:25:55,375 --> 00:25:57,500
- Nyla?

500
00:25:57,542 --> 00:25:59,625
- [chomping]

501
00:25:59,667 --> 00:26:03,166
- Whose my little
snuffly-wuffly?

502
00:26:03,208 --> 00:26:05,083
Whoa! Careful there!

503
00:26:05,125 --> 00:26:08,333
Okay, so who's got something
with the Avatar's scent on it?

504
00:26:08,375 --> 00:26:09,583
- I have Aang's staff.

505
00:26:11,583 --> 00:26:14,000
- [sniffing]

506
00:26:17,417 --> 00:26:20,750
[sniffing]

507
00:26:24,125 --> 00:26:26,458
[sniffing]

508
00:26:27,417 --> 00:26:29,917
[quiet growling]

509
00:26:29,959 --> 00:26:32,000
- Well, what does
that mean?

510
00:26:32,041 --> 00:26:34,125
- It means your
friend's gone.

511
00:26:34,166 --> 00:26:35,709
- We know he's gone.

512
00:26:35,750 --> 00:26:37,458
That's why we're
trying to find him.

513
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:39,208
- No, I mean
he's gone-gone.

514
00:26:39,250 --> 00:26:40,750
He doesn't exist.

515
00:26:45,458 --> 00:26:47,166
- [chattering]

516
00:26:47,208 --> 00:26:48,542
- Where are we, Momo?

517
00:26:50,792 --> 00:26:52,834
Maybe I'm in
the Spirit World?

518
00:26:55,542 --> 00:26:57,959
But, wait, you can see me.

519
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:00,625
We could both be in
the Spirit World.

520
00:27:04,542 --> 00:27:06,917
Nope, my bending works.

521
00:27:06,959 --> 00:27:09,166
Maybe if we climb to
the top of the island,

522
00:27:09,208 --> 00:27:10,834
we can figure out
where we are.

523
00:27:12,667 --> 00:27:15,000
- What do you mean
Aang doesn't exist?

524
00:27:15,041 --> 00:27:17,792
Do you mean he's,
you know, dead?

525
00:27:17,834 --> 00:27:20,583
- Nope, we could find
him if he were dead.

526
00:27:20,625 --> 00:27:22,375
Oh, it's a real
headscratcher.

527
00:27:22,417 --> 00:27:23,792
See ya.

528
00:27:23,834 --> 00:27:26,542
- Helpful. Real helpful.

529
00:27:26,583 --> 00:27:28,792
- Wait, I have another idea.

530
00:27:28,834 --> 00:27:30,625
There's only one
other person in this world

531
00:27:30,667 --> 00:27:32,792
who can help us
face the Firelord.

532
00:27:32,834 --> 00:27:34,875
I'll be right back
with a smell sample.

533
00:27:34,917 --> 00:27:36,959
- [insects buzzing]

534
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:39,583
- You saved your
uncle's sweaty sandal?

535
00:27:39,625 --> 00:27:42,041
- I think it's
kind of sweet.

536
00:27:42,083 --> 00:27:45,083
- [sniffing]

537
00:27:45,125 --> 00:27:46,125
- Let's do this.

538
00:27:49,333 --> 00:27:50,542
- ZUKO:
Hey, wait up!

539
00:27:54,709 --> 00:27:57,333
- [dramatic music]

540
00:27:57,375 --> 00:28:05,375
♪

541
00:28:10,792 --> 00:28:12,709
- [heavy thud]

542
00:28:15,583 --> 00:28:18,375
- SOKKA: We're going
to Ba Sing Se?

543
00:28:18,417 --> 00:28:20,333
- JUN: Your uncle is
somewhere beyond the wall.

544
00:28:20,375 --> 00:28:22,500
Nyla is getting twitchy,
so it can't be too far.

545
00:28:22,542 --> 00:28:24,125
Good luck.

546
00:28:28,500 --> 00:28:29,917
- It's been a long day.

547
00:28:29,959 --> 00:28:31,917
Let's camp and start
our search again at dawn.

548
00:28:35,583 --> 00:28:40,333
- [bird twittering]

549
00:28:40,375 --> 00:28:42,583
- It's a hexagon.

550
00:28:42,625 --> 00:28:44,250
- [chattering]

551
00:28:44,291 --> 00:28:46,166
- It doesn't seem
like normal rock.

552
00:28:50,667 --> 00:28:52,417
It's not made of earth.

553
00:28:52,458 --> 00:28:54,333
This is so strange.

554
00:28:54,375 --> 00:28:58,834
I wish some help right now.
I wish I had Roku.

555
00:28:58,875 --> 00:29:01,083
I do have Roku!

556
00:29:01,125 --> 00:29:05,041
- [slowly inhaling, exhaling]

557
00:29:05,083 --> 00:29:11,792
- ♪

558
00:29:11,834 --> 00:29:13,667
- You're right, Aang.

559
00:29:13,709 --> 00:29:16,417
All the past Avatars,

560
00:29:16,458 --> 00:29:20,917
all their experience and wisdom
is available to you,

561
00:29:20,959 --> 00:29:24,750
if you look deep
inside yourself.

562
00:29:24,792 --> 00:29:28,041
- So, where am I, Roku?
What is this place?

563
00:29:28,083 --> 00:29:31,542
- I don't know, Aang.

564
00:29:31,583 --> 00:29:36,125
But I see that you are lost in
more ways than one right now.

565
00:29:36,166 --> 00:29:37,041
- I am.

566
00:29:37,083 --> 00:29:38,500
I need to figure
out what to do

567
00:29:38,542 --> 00:29:39,834
once I face
the Firelord.

568
00:29:41,709 --> 00:29:44,291
- SOKKA: [snoring
loudly, sighing]

569
00:29:44,333 --> 00:29:45,458
- Huh?

570
00:29:45,500 --> 00:29:50,417
- ♪

571
00:29:50,458 --> 00:29:51,542
- APPA:
[bellowing]

572
00:29:51,583 --> 00:29:59,208
- ♪

573
00:29:59,250 --> 00:30:01,333
- Well, look who's here.

574
00:30:01,375 --> 00:30:03,083
[snorting laughter]

575
00:30:09,542 --> 00:30:11,792
- Everyone expects me to
take the Firelord's life.

576
00:30:11,834 --> 00:30:14,125
But I just don't know
if I can do that.

577
00:30:14,166 --> 00:30:19,667
- In my life, I tried to be
disciplined and show restraint,

578
00:30:19,709 --> 00:30:22,375
but it backfired
when Firelord Sozin

579
00:30:22,417 --> 00:30:26,709
took advantage of
my restraint and mercy.

580
00:30:26,750 --> 00:30:30,583
If had been more decisive,
and acted sooner,

581
00:30:30,625 --> 00:30:32,792
I could have stopped Sozin

582
00:30:32,834 --> 00:30:36,458
and stopped the war
before it started.

583
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:39,291
I offer you
this wisdom, Aang.

584
00:30:39,333 --> 00:30:41,959
You must be decisive.

585
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:47,625
- ♪

586
00:30:47,667 --> 00:30:50,041
- TOPH:
What's going on?

587
00:30:50,083 --> 00:30:52,041
We're surrounded
by old people.

588
00:30:52,083 --> 00:30:53,917
- KATARA:
Not just any old people,

589
00:30:53,959 --> 00:30:56,542
these are great masters
and friends of ours.

590
00:30:56,583 --> 00:30:58,208
Pakku.

591
00:30:58,250 --> 00:31:01,166
- It is respectful to
bow to an old master.

592
00:31:01,208 --> 00:31:05,709
But how about a hug
for your new grandfather?

593
00:31:05,750 --> 00:31:07,291
- That's so exciting!
- SOKKA: [gasps]

594
00:31:07,333 --> 00:31:09,000
- You and Gran Gran
must be so happy

595
00:31:09,041 --> 00:31:11,000
to have found
each other again.

596
00:31:11,041 --> 00:31:14,667
- I made her a new betrothal
necklace and everything.

597
00:31:14,709 --> 00:31:16,625
- Welcome to the family,
Gramp-Gramp!

598
00:31:16,667 --> 00:31:19,542
- You can still
just call me Pakku.

599
00:31:19,583 --> 00:31:23,041
- How about Gramp-Pakku?

600
00:31:23,083 --> 00:31:24,583
- No.

601
00:31:24,625 --> 00:31:27,667
- And this was Aang's
first firebending teacher.

602
00:31:27,709 --> 00:31:30,250
- Jeong-Jeong.

603
00:31:30,291 --> 00:31:31,583
- Master Piandao.

604
00:31:31,625 --> 00:31:33,458
- Hello, Sokka.

605
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:36,166
- So, wait, how do you
all know each other?

606
00:31:36,208 --> 00:31:39,208
- All old people know each
other, don't you know that?

607
00:31:39,250 --> 00:31:41,291
[snorting laughter]

608
00:31:41,333 --> 00:31:44,375
- We're all are part of the same
ancient secret society,

609
00:31:44,417 --> 00:31:48,250
a group that transcends the
divisions of the four nations.

610
00:31:48,291 --> 00:31:50,458
- The Order
of the White Lotus.

611
00:31:50,500 --> 00:31:52,583
- That's the one.

612
00:31:52,625 --> 00:31:55,417
- The White Lotus has always
been about philosophy,

613
00:31:55,458 --> 00:31:57,625
and beauty, and truth.

614
00:31:57,667 --> 00:31:59,875
But about a month ago,
a call went out

615
00:31:59,917 --> 00:32:02,333
that we were needed for
something important.

616
00:32:02,375 --> 00:32:05,542
- It came from
our Grand Lotus, your uncle,

617
00:32:05,583 --> 00:32:07,583
Iroh of the Fire Nation.

618
00:32:07,625 --> 00:32:09,375
- Well, that's who
we're looking for.

619
00:32:09,417 --> 00:32:11,208
- Then we'll take you to him.

620
00:32:11,250 --> 00:32:14,417
- Wait, someone's missing
from your group,

621
00:32:14,458 --> 00:32:17,083
someone very important.

622
00:32:17,125 --> 00:32:19,625
Where's Momo?

623
00:32:19,667 --> 00:32:23,041
- He's gone
and so is Aang.

624
00:32:23,083 --> 00:32:25,041
- Oh, well, so long
as they have each other,

625
00:32:25,083 --> 00:32:27,375
I'm sure we have
nothing to worry about.

626
00:32:27,417 --> 00:32:28,375
Let's go!

627
00:32:28,417 --> 00:32:31,125
[snorting laughter]

628
00:32:33,875 --> 00:32:36,166
- [chattering]

629
00:32:36,208 --> 00:32:40,375
- Avatar Kyoshi,
I need your wisdom.

630
00:32:40,417 --> 00:32:48,333
- ♪

631
00:32:48,375 --> 00:32:50,917
- In my day,
Chin The Conqueror

632
00:32:50,959 --> 00:32:52,959
threatened to throw
the world out of balance.

633
00:32:55,166 --> 00:33:00,458
I stopped him and the world
entered a great era of peace.

634
00:33:00,500 --> 00:33:01,792
- AANG: But you didn't
really kill Chin.

635
00:33:01,834 --> 00:33:03,333
Technically, he fell
to his own doom

636
00:33:03,375 --> 00:33:05,667
because he was too stubborn
to get out of the way.

637
00:33:05,709 --> 00:33:08,333
- Personally, I don't
really see the difference.

638
00:33:08,375 --> 00:33:10,083
But I assure you,

639
00:33:10,125 --> 00:33:13,417
I would have done whatever
it took to stop Chin.

640
00:33:13,458 --> 00:33:15,959
I offer you this
wisdom, Aang.

641
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,333
Only justice will
bring peace.

642
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:23,625
- I knew I shouldn't
have asked Kyoshi.

643
00:33:26,375 --> 00:33:28,083
- SOKKA: So, Bumi,
how did you end up escaping

644
00:33:28,125 --> 00:33:30,083
your imprisonment
in Omashu?

645
00:33:30,125 --> 00:33:32,542
- Escape?
I didn't escape.

646
00:33:32,583 --> 00:33:35,083
Everybody else escaped.

647
00:33:35,125 --> 00:33:37,166
There I was,
back in Omashu,

648
00:33:37,208 --> 00:33:40,250
waiting for
just the right moment.

649
00:33:40,291 --> 00:33:41,875
I didn't know
what or when,

650
00:33:41,917 --> 00:33:45,500
but I knew I'd know
it when I knew it.

651
00:33:45,542 --> 00:33:46,750
An eclipse!

652
00:33:46,792 --> 00:33:48,375
That'll do it!

653
00:33:48,417 --> 00:33:50,375
[straining]

654
00:33:50,417 --> 00:33:58,625
- ♪

655
00:33:58,667 --> 00:34:00,417
- What do you think
you're doing?

656
00:34:00,458 --> 00:34:02,041
[grunts]

657
00:34:02,083 --> 00:34:03,750
[grunts]

658
00:34:05,166 --> 00:34:07,083
- Taking back my city.

659
00:34:07,125 --> 00:34:10,375
You've got no firepower
and it's payback time!

660
00:34:10,417 --> 00:34:18,417
- ♪

661
00:34:25,333 --> 00:34:26,375
- ♪

662
00:34:27,375 --> 00:34:32,375
♪

663
00:34:42,291 --> 00:34:43,375
♪

664
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,542
- [straining]

665
00:34:46,583 --> 00:34:55,625
- ♪

666
00:34:55,667 --> 00:34:57,250
- [snorting laughter]

667
00:34:57,291 --> 00:34:59,917
[chomps, chewing]

668
00:34:59,959 --> 00:35:04,166
- Wow, you took back your whole
city all by yourself.

669
00:35:04,208 --> 00:35:06,250
- BUMI:
So what about you, guys?

670
00:35:06,291 --> 00:35:09,000
Did you do anything interesting
on the day of the eclipse?

671
00:35:10,417 --> 00:35:13,291
- Nah.
- No, not really.

672
00:35:13,333 --> 00:35:15,542
- I need to look
deep inside myself.

673
00:35:15,583 --> 00:35:25,041
- ♪

674
00:35:25,083 --> 00:35:27,500
- I am Avatar Kuruk.

675
00:35:27,542 --> 00:35:29,166
When I was young,

676
00:35:29,208 --> 00:35:34,500
I was always a "go with
the flow" kind of Avatar.

677
00:35:34,542 --> 00:35:36,875
People seemed to work
out their own problems,

678
00:35:36,917 --> 00:35:39,500
and there was peace
and good times in the world.

679
00:35:42,125 --> 00:35:44,792
But then, I lost
the woman I loved

680
00:35:44,834 --> 00:35:49,583
to Koh, the face stealer.

681
00:35:49,625 --> 00:35:51,291
It was my fault.

682
00:35:51,333 --> 00:35:53,959
If I had been more attentive
and more active,

683
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:56,333
I could have saved her.

684
00:35:56,375 --> 00:36:00,750
Aang, you must actively
shape your own destiny,

685
00:36:00,792 --> 00:36:02,959
and the destiny
of the world.

686
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,000
- ♪

687
00:36:13,542 --> 00:36:15,125
- [boulder lowers]

688
00:36:15,166 --> 00:36:18,583
- Well, here we are.
Welcome to old people camp.

689
00:36:20,709 --> 00:36:23,250
- Where? Where is he?

690
00:36:23,291 --> 00:36:25,542
- Your uncle's in there,
Prince Zuko.

691
00:36:25,583 --> 00:36:30,583
- ♪

692
00:36:36,750 --> 00:36:37,959
- Are you okay?

693
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:40,000
- No, I'm not okay.

694
00:36:40,041 --> 00:36:41,917
My uncle hates me,
I know it.

695
00:36:41,959 --> 00:36:45,000
He loved me and supported me
in every way he could,

696
00:36:45,041 --> 00:36:47,166
and I still turned
against him.

697
00:36:47,208 --> 00:36:48,875
How can I even face him?

698
00:36:48,917 --> 00:36:52,125
- Zuko, you're sorry for
what you did, right?

699
00:36:52,166 --> 00:36:53,500
- More sorry than I've
been about anything

700
00:36:53,542 --> 00:36:55,208
in my entire life.

701
00:36:55,250 --> 00:36:57,875
- Then he'll forgive you.
He will.

702
00:36:57,917 --> 00:37:03,083
- ♪

703
00:37:03,125 --> 00:37:06,625
- [heavy sigh]

704
00:37:06,667 --> 00:37:08,000
Uncle...

705
00:37:08,041 --> 00:37:12,333
- [loud snoring]

706
00:37:12,375 --> 00:37:18,375
- ♪

707
00:37:23,667 --> 00:37:25,417
- AANG: All these
past Avatars,

708
00:37:25,458 --> 00:37:27,542
they keep telling me
I'm gonna have to do it.

709
00:37:27,583 --> 00:37:29,875
They don't get it.
- [chattering]

710
00:37:29,917 --> 00:37:32,041
- You're right, maybe
an Air Nomad Avatar

711
00:37:32,083 --> 00:37:34,166
will understand where
I'm coming from.

712
00:37:34,208 --> 00:37:36,333
- [chattering]

713
00:37:36,375 --> 00:37:37,625
- I know you can't
really talk.

714
00:37:37,667 --> 00:37:39,917
Pretending you can
just helps me think.

715
00:37:39,959 --> 00:37:41,542
- [chattering]

716
00:37:41,583 --> 00:37:44,625
- I'm going to pretend
I didn't pretend to hear that.

717
00:37:44,667 --> 00:37:52,792
- ♪

718
00:37:52,834 --> 00:37:55,792
- I am Avatar Yangchen,
young Airbender.

719
00:37:55,834 --> 00:37:58,250
- Avatar Yangchen,
the monks always taught me

720
00:37:58,291 --> 00:38:00,041
that all life is sacred,

721
00:38:00,083 --> 00:38:01,834
even the life of
the tiniest spider-fly

722
00:38:01,875 --> 00:38:03,333
caught in its own web.

723
00:38:03,375 --> 00:38:06,542
- Yes, all life is sacred.

724
00:38:06,583 --> 00:38:08,750
- I know. I'm even
a vegetarian.

725
00:38:08,792 --> 00:38:10,291
I've always tried
to solve my problems

726
00:38:10,333 --> 00:38:12,083
by being quick or clever,

727
00:38:12,125 --> 00:38:14,917
and I've only had to use
violence for necessary defense,

728
00:38:14,959 --> 00:38:17,625
and I've certainly never
used it to take a life.

729
00:38:17,667 --> 00:38:21,667
- Avatar Aang, I know that
you're a gentle spirit,

730
00:38:21,709 --> 00:38:24,125
and the monks have
taught you well,

731
00:38:24,166 --> 00:38:26,375
but this isn't about you.

732
00:38:26,417 --> 00:38:28,041
This is about the world.

733
00:38:28,083 --> 00:38:30,750
- But the monks taught me,
that I have to detach myself

734
00:38:30,792 --> 00:38:33,000
from the world
so my spirit could be free.

735
00:38:33,041 --> 00:38:37,041
- Many great and wise Air Nomads
have detached themselves

736
00:38:37,083 --> 00:38:39,917
and achieved spiritual
enlightenment.

737
00:38:39,959 --> 00:38:42,208
But the Avatar
can never do it,

738
00:38:42,250 --> 00:38:45,834
because your sole duty
is to the world.

739
00:38:45,875 --> 00:38:49,000
Here is my wisdom for you--

740
00:38:49,041 --> 00:38:51,250
selfless duty calls
you to sacrifice

741
00:38:51,291 --> 00:38:53,875
your own spiritual needs

742
00:38:53,917 --> 00:38:58,083
and do whatever it takes
to protect the world.

743
00:39:00,625 --> 00:39:03,333
- [chattering]

744
00:39:03,375 --> 00:39:05,291
- I guess I don't have
a choice, Momo.

745
00:39:05,333 --> 00:39:07,125
I have to kill
the Firelord.

746
00:39:10,083 --> 00:39:12,166
- ♪

747
00:39:12,208 --> 00:39:13,583
- [snoring loudly]

748
00:39:13,625 --> 00:39:15,166
Hmmm...

749
00:39:15,208 --> 00:39:17,625
[yawning loudly]

750
00:39:22,667 --> 00:39:28,500
- Uncle, I know you must have
mixed feelings about seeing me.

751
00:39:28,542 --> 00:39:33,625
But I want you to know
I am so, so sorry, Uncle.

752
00:39:33,667 --> 00:39:37,041
I am so sorry and ashamed
of what I did.

753
00:39:37,083 --> 00:39:39,875
I don't know how I can ever
make it up to you, but I--

754
00:39:39,917 --> 00:39:46,125
- ♪

755
00:39:46,166 --> 00:39:48,458
- How can you forgive
me so easily?

756
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:50,333
I thought you would
be furious with me.

757
00:39:50,375 --> 00:39:53,917
- I was never angry
with you.

758
00:39:53,959 --> 00:39:58,625
I was sad, because I was
afraid you'd lost your way.

759
00:39:58,667 --> 00:40:01,500
- I did lose my way.

760
00:40:01,542 --> 00:40:05,750
- But you've found
it again...

761
00:40:05,792 --> 00:40:08,750
and you did it
by yourself,

762
00:40:08,792 --> 00:40:13,750
and I am so happy you
found your way here.

763
00:40:13,792 --> 00:40:16,250
- It wasn't that
hard, Uncle.

764
00:40:16,291 --> 00:40:18,875
You have a pretty
strong scent.

765
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:21,542
- SQUIRREL:
[chattering]

766
00:40:21,583 --> 00:40:23,291
- BIRDS:
[twittering]

767
00:40:25,917 --> 00:40:26,750
- [distant rumbling]

768
00:40:26,792 --> 00:40:29,041
- [loud yawn]

769
00:40:29,083 --> 00:40:31,250
- [louder rumbling]

770
00:40:31,291 --> 00:40:35,083
- Wait, is it just me or are
those mountains getting bigger?

771
00:40:35,125 --> 00:40:36,542
- [chattering]

772
00:40:45,875 --> 00:40:47,917
- They're not getting larger,
they're getting closer.

773
00:40:47,959 --> 00:40:49,375
- [chattering]

774
00:40:51,500 --> 00:40:52,875
- The whole island
is moving!

775
00:40:52,917 --> 00:40:59,667
- ♪

776
00:40:59,709 --> 00:41:00,959
- [chattering]

777
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:07,000
- ♪

778
00:41:15,917 --> 00:41:16,583
- ♪

779
00:41:16,625 --> 00:41:18,083
- [gasping for air]

780
00:41:18,125 --> 00:41:19,375
- [chattering]

781
00:41:19,417 --> 00:41:21,000
- It's amazing, Momo!

782
00:41:21,041 --> 00:41:22,875
The biggest animal
in the world!

783
00:41:22,917 --> 00:41:25,291
I've gotta swim
around and find its face.

784
00:41:25,333 --> 00:41:31,333
- ♪

785
00:41:36,667 --> 00:41:39,625
- ZUKO: Uncle, you're the only
person other than the Avatar

786
00:41:39,667 --> 00:41:42,625
who can possibly
defeat the Fatherlord.

787
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:44,291
- You mean the Firelord?

788
00:41:44,333 --> 00:41:45,875
- That's what I just said.

789
00:41:45,917 --> 00:41:47,875
- Hmmm...

790
00:41:47,917 --> 00:41:50,125
- We need you to
come with us.

791
00:41:50,166 --> 00:41:51,709
- No, Zuko.

792
00:41:51,750 --> 00:41:53,625
It won't turn out well.

793
00:41:53,667 --> 00:41:56,375
- You can beat him
and we'll be there to help.

794
00:41:56,417 --> 00:41:59,166
- Even if I did defeat Ozai,

795
00:41:59,208 --> 00:42:01,834
and I don't know
that I could,

796
00:42:01,875 --> 00:42:05,000
it would be the wrong
way to end a war.

797
00:42:05,041 --> 00:42:08,625
History will see it as just
more senseless violence,

798
00:42:08,667 --> 00:42:11,834
a brother killing a brother
to grab power.

799
00:42:11,875 --> 00:42:14,625
The only way for this
war to end peacefully

800
00:42:14,667 --> 00:42:18,875
is for the Avatar
to defeat the Firelord.

801
00:42:18,917 --> 00:42:21,500
- And then...then would
you come and take

802
00:42:21,542 --> 00:42:23,625
your rightful place
on the throne?

803
00:42:23,667 --> 00:42:27,667
- No. Someone new must
take the throne--

804
00:42:27,709 --> 00:42:33,250
an idealist with a pure heart
and unquestionable honor.

805
00:42:33,291 --> 00:42:36,250
It has to be you,
Prince Zuko.

806
00:42:36,291 --> 00:42:38,333
- Unquestionable honor?

807
00:42:38,375 --> 00:42:40,166
But I've made
so many mistakes.

808
00:42:40,208 --> 00:42:42,667
- Yes, you have.

809
00:42:42,709 --> 00:42:45,792
You've struggled
and you've suffered,

810
00:42:45,834 --> 00:42:48,500
but you have always
followed your own path.

811
00:42:48,542 --> 00:42:51,083
You restored
your own honor,

812
00:42:51,125 --> 00:42:56,333
and only you can restore
the honor of the Fire Nation.

813
00:42:56,375 --> 00:42:58,375
- I'll try, Uncle.

814
00:42:58,417 --> 00:43:02,000
- Well, what if Aang
doesn't come back?

815
00:43:02,041 --> 00:43:06,166
- Sozin's Comet is arriving
and our destinies are upon us.

816
00:43:06,208 --> 00:43:09,417
Aang will face
the Firelord.

817
00:43:09,458 --> 00:43:11,834
When I was a boy,
I had a vision

818
00:43:11,875 --> 00:43:15,333
that I would one day
take Ba Sing Se.

819
00:43:15,375 --> 00:43:17,709
Only now do I see
that my destiny

820
00:43:17,750 --> 00:43:21,250
is to take it back
from the Fire Nation,

821
00:43:21,291 --> 00:43:25,625
so the Earth Kingdom
can be free again.

822
00:43:25,667 --> 00:43:28,667
- That's why you gathered
the members of the White Lotus.

823
00:43:28,709 --> 00:43:30,750
- Yes.

824
00:43:30,792 --> 00:43:34,166
Zuko, you must return
to the Fire Nation,

825
00:43:34,208 --> 00:43:36,000
so that when
the Firelord falls,

826
00:43:36,041 --> 00:43:41,250
you can assume the throne
and restore peace and order.

827
00:43:41,291 --> 00:43:44,417
But Azula will be there
waiting for you.

828
00:43:44,458 --> 00:43:46,542
- I can handle Azula.

829
00:43:46,583 --> 00:43:50,041
- Not alone.
You'll need help.

830
00:43:50,083 --> 00:43:51,792
- You're right.

831
00:43:51,834 --> 00:43:55,000
Katara, how would you like to
help me put Azula in her place?

832
00:43:55,041 --> 00:43:56,792
- It would be my pleasure.

833
00:43:56,834 --> 00:44:00,375
- What about us?
What's our destiny today?

834
00:44:00,417 --> 00:44:02,750
- What do you think it is?

835
00:44:02,792 --> 00:44:05,375
- I think that even though
we don't know where Aang is,

836
00:44:05,417 --> 00:44:08,667
we need to do everything we can
to stop the airship fleet.

837
00:44:08,709 --> 00:44:11,250
- And that means, when Aang
does face the Firelord,

838
00:44:11,291 --> 00:44:13,625
we'll be right there
if he needs us.

839
00:44:13,667 --> 00:44:19,291
- ♪

840
00:44:19,333 --> 00:44:20,709
- Nothing runs
faster over land

841
00:44:20,750 --> 00:44:23,709
or swims quicker
than a giant eel-hound.

842
00:44:23,750 --> 00:44:25,667
The airship base
is on a small island

843
00:44:25,709 --> 00:44:27,792
just off the Earth
Kingdom shore.

844
00:44:27,834 --> 00:44:29,542
You should be able
to intercept the fleet

845
00:44:29,583 --> 00:44:32,208
within a day's journey.

846
00:44:32,250 --> 00:44:33,792
- Thank you, master.

847
00:44:33,834 --> 00:44:39,875
- ♪

848
00:44:39,917 --> 00:44:43,250
- So, if I'm gonna be Firelord
after the war's over,

849
00:44:43,291 --> 00:44:44,542
what are you gonna do?

850
00:44:44,583 --> 00:44:47,750
- After I reconquer
Ba Sing Se,

851
00:44:47,792 --> 00:44:50,792
I am going to
reconquer my tea shop

852
00:44:50,834 --> 00:44:54,333
and I am going to play
Pai Sho every day.

853
00:44:58,750 --> 00:45:02,750
- Goodbye, General Iroh.
- Goodbye, everyone.

854
00:45:02,792 --> 00:45:07,792
Today, destiny is
our friend. I know it.

855
00:45:07,834 --> 00:45:15,834
- ♪

856
00:45:22,750 --> 00:45:23,750
- ♪

857
00:45:24,792 --> 00:45:32,041
♪

858
00:45:32,083 --> 00:45:33,834
[dramatic music]

859
00:45:33,875 --> 00:45:41,875
♪

860
00:45:48,250 --> 00:45:49,333
♪

861
00:45:49,375 --> 00:45:51,417
- A lion-turtle.

862
00:45:54,333 --> 00:45:56,208
Maybe you can help me.

863
00:45:56,250 --> 00:45:59,709
Everyone, even
my own past lives

864
00:45:59,750 --> 00:46:03,500
are expecting me to
end someone's life.

865
00:46:03,542 --> 00:46:05,250
But I don't know
if I can do it.

866
00:46:05,291 --> 00:46:08,583
- LION-TURTLE: The true mind
can weather all the lies

867
00:46:08,625 --> 00:46:11,875
and illusions
without being lost.

868
00:46:11,917 --> 00:46:15,375
The true heart can tough
the poison of hatred

869
00:46:15,417 --> 00:46:18,000
without being harmed.

870
00:46:18,041 --> 00:46:22,041
Since beginning-less time,
darkness thrives in the void,

871
00:46:22,083 --> 00:46:26,041
but always yields
to purifying light.

872
00:46:26,083 --> 00:46:29,083
♪

873
00:46:36,417 --> 00:46:38,166
- Wait for him.

874
00:46:38,208 --> 00:46:40,041
He will come.

875
00:46:40,083 --> 00:46:43,083
♪

876
00:46:50,917 --> 00:46:55,000
- It's time for this
world to end in fire

877
00:46:55,041 --> 00:46:59,208
and for a new world
to be born from the ashes.

878
00:46:59,250 --> 00:47:03,166
- [dramatic music]

879
00:47:03,208 --> 00:47:06,208
♪

880
00:47:20,208 --> 00:47:23,625
♪

881
00:47:26,583 --> 00:47:33,208
♪

882
00:47:33,250 --> 00:47:37,625
- [comet roaring]

883
00:47:42,500 --> 00:47:44,542
- APPA:
[bellowing]

884
00:47:46,667 --> 00:47:49,667
- Zuko, don't worry.
We can take Azula.

885
00:47:49,709 --> 00:47:51,291
- I'm not worried
about her.

886
00:47:51,333 --> 00:47:53,125
I'm worried about Aang.

887
00:47:53,166 --> 00:47:56,250
What if he doesn't have the guts
to take out my father?

888
00:47:56,291 --> 00:47:57,291
What if he loses?

889
00:47:57,333 --> 00:47:59,417
- Aang won't lose.

890
00:47:59,458 --> 00:48:01,166
He's gonna come back.

891
00:48:02,250 --> 00:48:03,834
He has to.

892
00:48:03,875 --> 00:48:08,917
- [dramatic music]

893
00:48:08,959 --> 00:48:14,959
♪

894
00:48:19,792 --> 00:48:21,083
- [tooth crunches]

895
00:48:21,125 --> 00:48:22,667
[spits]

896
00:48:22,709 --> 00:48:25,625
What am I holding?

897
00:48:25,667 --> 00:48:28,083
- A cherry pit, Princess.

898
00:48:28,125 --> 00:48:28,792
- Correct.

899
00:48:28,834 --> 00:48:30,625
And what day is this?

900
00:48:30,667 --> 00:48:32,750
- It is the day
of your coronation.

901
00:48:32,792 --> 00:48:34,250
- Yes, it is.

902
00:48:34,291 --> 00:48:35,792
So, please, tell me why,

903
00:48:35,834 --> 00:48:37,875
on the most important
day of my life,

904
00:48:37,917 --> 00:48:40,291
you decided to leave
a pit in my cherry?

905
00:48:40,333 --> 00:48:44,125
- It wasn't a decision,
it was just a small mistake.

906
00:48:44,166 --> 00:48:45,500
- Small?

907
00:48:45,542 --> 00:48:47,625
Do you realize what
could have happened

908
00:48:47,667 --> 00:48:49,083
if I hadn't sensed
the pit in time?

909
00:48:49,125 --> 00:48:52,000
- I suppose you
could have choked?

910
00:48:52,041 --> 00:48:56,625
- Yes, then you understand
the severity of your crime.

911
00:48:56,667 --> 00:48:58,291
- I understand, Princess.

912
00:48:58,333 --> 00:48:59,917
Please, forgive me.

913
00:48:59,959 --> 00:49:01,375
- Oh, very well.

914
00:49:01,417 --> 00:49:05,125
Since it is a special day,
I will show mercy.

915
00:49:05,166 --> 00:49:06,500
You are banished.

916
00:49:06,542 --> 00:49:08,125
Leave this palace
immediately.

917
00:49:11,208 --> 00:49:12,375
What are you
all looking at?

918
00:49:12,417 --> 00:49:14,542
I have two feet
that need scrubbing.

919
00:49:14,583 --> 00:49:16,875
And make sure you get
in between the toes.

920
00:49:16,917 --> 00:49:18,417
I won't have my
first day as Firelord

921
00:49:18,458 --> 00:49:20,709
marred by poor
foot hygiene.

922
00:49:25,375 --> 00:49:29,375
- It's weird to say, but the
comet actually looks beautiful.

923
00:49:29,417 --> 00:49:32,291
- Too bad the Firelord's about
to use it to destroy the world.

924
00:49:32,333 --> 00:49:34,333
- ♪

925
00:49:47,250 --> 00:49:48,291
- ♪

926
00:49:49,291 --> 00:49:58,083
♪

927
00:49:58,125 --> 00:50:01,500
- SOKKA: We're too late!
The fleet's already taking off!

928
00:50:01,542 --> 00:50:03,875
- TOPH: Then we're
taking off, too.

929
00:50:03,917 --> 00:50:05,417
Where's the closest airship?
- It's right--

930
00:50:05,458 --> 00:50:06,625
- ALL:
[gasping]

931
00:50:06,667 --> 00:50:13,166
- ♪

932
00:50:13,208 --> 00:50:14,125
- [grunts]

933
00:50:14,166 --> 00:50:17,166
- ♪

934
00:50:29,083 --> 00:50:30,125
- ♪

935
00:50:31,208 --> 00:50:40,709
♪

936
00:50:45,542 --> 00:50:47,000
- You sent for us,
Princess?

937
00:50:47,041 --> 00:50:48,125
Is everything all right?

938
00:50:48,166 --> 00:50:50,542
- Actually, everything's
not all right.

939
00:50:50,583 --> 00:50:52,709
Do you know how long
it took you to get here?

940
00:50:52,750 --> 00:50:54,542
- Uh, few minutes,
I guess.

941
00:50:54,583 --> 00:50:56,458
- AZULA:
Five, to be precise--

942
00:50:56,500 --> 00:50:58,458
in which time an assassin
could have snuck in,

943
00:50:58,500 --> 00:51:01,291
done away with me,
and been on his merry way.

944
00:51:01,333 --> 00:51:02,917
- My apologies, Princess.

945
00:51:02,959 --> 00:51:05,458
- Is this how you plan to
treat your new Firelord--

946
00:51:05,500 --> 00:51:07,625
with tardiness
and disloyalty?

947
00:51:07,667 --> 00:51:09,500
- The Dai Lee would
never betray you.

948
00:51:09,542 --> 00:51:11,667
- And I'm sure that's just
what you told Long Feng

949
00:51:11,709 --> 00:51:14,834
before you turned
against him and joined me.

950
00:51:14,875 --> 00:51:17,625
You're all banished!
- But--

951
00:51:17,667 --> 00:51:19,208
- AZULA:
Goodbye!

952
00:51:24,709 --> 00:51:26,959
Please send in the next
group on your way out.

953
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:31,000
- ♪

954
00:51:38,709 --> 00:51:40,625
- Shhhh...

955
00:51:43,250 --> 00:51:45,250
- [rapping on metal door]

956
00:51:45,291 --> 00:51:46,917
- [metal door slams]

957
00:51:48,667 --> 00:51:57,583
- ♪

958
00:51:57,625 --> 00:51:58,709
- Oh!

959
00:51:58,750 --> 00:52:02,750
- ♪

960
00:52:13,667 --> 00:52:14,375
- ♪

961
00:52:14,417 --> 00:52:15,959
- [grunting, groaning]

962
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:22,417
- ♪

963
00:52:22,458 --> 00:52:25,166
- That's how it's done.
- SOKKA: Good work, Toph.

964
00:52:25,208 --> 00:52:26,750
Time to take control
of the ship.

965
00:52:26,792 --> 00:52:28,000
Take the wheel.

966
00:52:28,041 --> 00:52:29,208
- That's a great idea.

967
00:52:29,250 --> 00:52:31,667
Let the blind girl steer
the giant airship.

968
00:52:31,709 --> 00:52:33,875
- I was talking to Suki.

969
00:52:33,917 --> 00:52:36,166
- That would make
a lot more sense.

970
00:52:36,208 --> 00:52:38,208
- What are we gonna do
about the rest of the crew?

971
00:52:38,250 --> 00:52:39,834
- Take us down closer
to the water.

972
00:52:39,875 --> 00:52:41,291
I've got an idea.

973
00:52:44,583 --> 00:52:47,208
[clears throat]
Attention, crew,

974
00:52:47,250 --> 00:52:49,000
this is your
captain speaking.

975
00:52:49,041 --> 00:52:51,875
Everyone please report to
the bomb bay immediately,

976
00:52:51,917 --> 00:52:55,291
for hot cakes
and sweet cream.

977
00:52:55,333 --> 00:52:58,542
We have a very special
birthday to celebrate.

978
00:52:58,583 --> 00:53:05,291
- ♪

979
00:53:05,333 --> 00:53:08,208
- [mixed conversations]

980
00:53:08,250 --> 00:53:10,250
- Hey, I'm Quin Lee.

981
00:53:10,291 --> 00:53:12,333
I work up in
Communications.

982
00:53:12,375 --> 00:53:13,625
- Oh, hi.

983
00:53:13,667 --> 00:53:15,583
I work down in
the engine room.

984
00:53:15,625 --> 00:53:18,125
That's probably why
we've never met before.

985
00:53:18,166 --> 00:53:19,083
Big airship, you know?

986
00:53:19,125 --> 00:53:21,542
- Uh-huh.
- Yep.

987
00:53:21,583 --> 00:53:23,959
- So, do you know
whose birthday it is?

988
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:27,458
- I can't believe that captain
remembered my birthday!

989
00:53:27,500 --> 00:53:29,125
He really does care!

990
00:53:29,166 --> 00:53:31,792
- CREW:
[screaming]

991
00:53:31,834 --> 00:53:33,750
- [water splashing]

992
00:53:33,792 --> 00:53:36,083
- CREW:
[gasping for air]

993
00:53:37,917 --> 00:53:40,208
- Happy birthday.

994
00:53:40,250 --> 00:53:43,959
- ♪

995
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:46,667
- Firelord Ozai,
here we come.

996
00:53:46,709 --> 00:53:49,500
- [dramatic music]

997
00:53:49,542 --> 00:53:53,250
♪

998
00:53:56,208 --> 00:53:58,166
- [dramatic music]

999
00:53:58,208 --> 00:54:01,500
♪

1000
00:54:01,542 --> 00:54:03,834
- Azula, we heard
what happened.

1001
00:54:03,875 --> 00:54:06,250
- Why have you banished
all your servants...

1002
00:54:06,291 --> 00:54:08,208
- ...all your
Dai Lee agents...

1003
00:54:08,250 --> 00:54:10,333
- ...and the Imperial
Firebenders?

1004
00:54:10,375 --> 00:54:12,041
- None of them
could be trusted.

1005
00:54:12,083 --> 00:54:14,917
Sooner or later they all
would have betrayed me--

1006
00:54:14,959 --> 00:54:16,875
just like Mai
and Ty Lee did.

1007
00:54:16,917 --> 00:54:20,375
- BOTH: Azula, we are concerned
for you and your well-being.

1008
00:54:22,166 --> 00:54:25,625
- My father asked you to come
here and talk to me didn't he?

1009
00:54:25,667 --> 00:54:27,041
He thinks I can't handle

1010
00:54:27,083 --> 00:54:28,834
the responsibility
of being Firelord.

1011
00:54:28,875 --> 00:54:30,375
But I will be
the greatest leader

1012
00:54:30,417 --> 00:54:32,458
in Fire Nation history.

1013
00:54:32,500 --> 00:54:33,959
- I'm sure you will.

1014
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:36,333
But considering everything
that's happened today...

1015
00:54:36,375 --> 00:54:39,875
- ...perhaps it's best if
you postpone your coronation.

1016
00:54:39,917 --> 00:54:41,917
- What? Which one
of you just said that?

1017
00:54:44,458 --> 00:54:45,750
- What a shame.

1018
00:54:45,792 --> 00:54:48,166
There's only one way
to resolve this.

1019
00:54:48,208 --> 00:54:50,291
You two must duel
each other.

1020
00:54:50,333 --> 00:54:53,208
I order you to fight
an Agni Kai.

1021
00:54:53,250 --> 00:54:56,125
- But...
- BOTH: We're not Firebenders.

1022
00:54:56,166 --> 00:54:58,208
- All right, fine.

1023
00:54:58,250 --> 00:55:01,250
Lo, you're banished.
Li, you can stay.

1024
00:55:01,291 --> 00:55:04,333
- But, I'm Li.
So who is banished?

1025
00:55:06,083 --> 00:55:10,083
- ♪

1026
00:55:18,250 --> 00:55:22,458
- Ba Sing Se, the Order of
